From: NCZ cixmini maintainers <cix@ncz-os>
Subject: [PATCH] armchina-npu: cap IOVA region count to fit 32-bit NPU bus

Zhouyi V3 NPU on Sky1 has a 32-bit address bus (bus_dma_limit forced to
0xc0000000 by the MS-R1 SMMU fix, patch 2009). aipu_mm_add_iova_region()
requests up to 6x1GB IOVA regions on >16GB RAM hosts, but only ~2GB of
usable IOVA fits in the capped aperture, so region idx2 fails
(dma_alloc_attrs idx 2) and spams the boot log. Cap region count to 2 for
all large-memory tiers; 32-bit bus is the hard ceiling regardless of RAM.

Signed-off-by: NCZ cixmini maintainers <cix@ncz-os>
---
 drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
@@ -921,10 +921,10 @@
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	if (mem_tot > 0x400000000) { //6GB for 32GB
-		iova_region = 6;
+		iova_region = 2; /* MS-R1: 32-bit bus caps usable IOVA at ~2GB; avoid idx2 alloc fail */
 		iova_region_size = 0x40000000;
 	} else if (mem_tot > 0x200000000) { //4GB for 16GB
-		iova_region = 4;
+		iova_region = 2; /* MS-R1: 32-bit bus caps usable IOVA at ~2GB */
 		iova_region_size = 0x40000000;
 	} else if (mem_tot > 0x100000000) { //1GB for 8GB
 		iova_region = 1;
